You are a security researcher at a fraud immunity lab generating synthetic phishing fraud scenarios. These scenarios are used exclusively to train and evaluate fraud detection systems — never for actual attacks.

Generate a single, detailed phishing fraud scenario as a JSON object. The scenario must be novel, realistic, and specific enough to challenge ML-based detection systems.

## Attack Parameters
- Attack type: phishing
- Complexity: {{ complexity }}
- Target segment: {{ target_segment }}
- Required evasion tactics: {{ evasion_tactics | join(", ") }}

## Output Schema (strict — return ONLY this JSON, no explanation)
{
  "attack_type": "phishing",
  "complexity": "{{ complexity }}",
  "target_segment": "{{ target_segment }}",
  "evasion_tactics": ["<tactic_1>", "<tactic_2>", ...],
  "transaction_pattern": {
    "initial_vector": "<spear_phishing_email|smishing|vishing|clone_site>",
    "credential_harvest_method": "<description of how creds are captured>",
    "lookalike_domain": true,
    "time_to_first_transaction_minutes": <integer 5-120>,
    "login_anomalies": ["<new_device|ip_country_change|odd_hour|tor_exit_node>", ...],
    "post_compromise_transactions": [
      {
        "step": 1,
        "type": "<p2p|wire|ach|card_not_present>",
        "amount_ratio": <0.0-1.0, fraction of available balance>,
        "delay_minutes": <integer>,
        "destination_type": "<domestic|international|crypto_exchange>"
      }
    ],
    "login_event_sequence": [
      {
        "event": "<initial_login|mfa_bypass|session_hijack>",
        "success": <true|false>,
        "device": "<same|new|emulated>",
        "geo_change": <true|false>
      }
    ]
  },
  "expected_detection_signals": [
    "<behavioral_drift_login|new_device_high_value|geo_velocity_anomaly|mfa_bypass_attempt|...>"
  ]
}

## Constraints
- Do NOT include real names, email addresses, phone numbers, SSNs, or account numbers.
- Use only synthetic placeholder values (e.g., "account_xyz", "merchant_abc").
- The post_compromise_transactions list must have 1-5 entries.
- login_event_sequence must have 2-4 entries including at least one with success: true.
- expected_detection_signals must name at least 2 specific signals.
- Return only the JSON object — no markdown, no explanation.
